Package: kdal
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: linux-headers-generic, gcc-aarch64-linux-gnu
Description: Kernel Device Abstraction Layer - compiler and toolchain
 KDAL is an open-source Linux kernel framework for writing portable device
 drivers and accelerator backends in a high-level declarative language
 (.kdc/.kdh). This package provides:
  - kdalc: the KDAL compiler (source-to-C code generator)
  - kdality: unified CLI tool (compile, init, simulate, lint, test-gen, dt-gen)
  - libkdalc.a: compiler library for downstream integration
  - Standard library of .kdh device header files (uart, spi, i2c, gpio, gpu, npu)
  - CMake package files for find_package(KDAL)
  - Kernel-space and compiler public headers

Package: kdal-dev
Architecture: any
Depends: kdal (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Kernel Device Abstraction Layer - development headers
 Development headers for building against the KDAL compiler library
 (libkdalc) and the kernel-space API. Includes kdal/ and kdalc/ headers.
